The paper describes a system that collects data through wireless sensor networks and uses logical reasoning to infer information about patients' well-being and predict possible health evolutions. This involves the use of machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The system also involves the use of databases and data management techniques, which are associated with the cs.DB sub-category. Additionally, the system is focused on healthcare and monitoring patients in their home environment, which suggests a connection to the cs.HC sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses issues related to privacy and security, which could be relevant to the cs.CY sub-category.
